div.div:
Lopy4 Pins
(28 pins, pin 1 is top left viewed from above, pin 28 top right)
Pin 5 = GPIO4/TX1 - TX to UHF receiver
Pin 6 = GPIO15/RX1 - RX from UHF receiver
Pin 11 = GPIO12 - RX from SIM800L
Pin 12 = GPIO13 - TX to SIM800L
Pin 13 = GPIO22 - Rst to SIM800L
Pin 17 = GPIO38 = Battery test - ADC mode, 0dB attn
Pin 27 = Gnd
Pin 28 = Vin = top right = 5v

div.div:
Connectors
UHF reader - 4-pin JST on right, locating slot facing right board edge
Power - 3 by 4-pin JST on left, locating slots facing left board edge
Battery - 2-pin JST top left, locating slot facing down
WiFi antenna - bottom left on Lopy4
GSM antenna - top left on SIM800L module
Lora antenna - top left on Lopy4
GPS antenna - on Pytrack2 board
USB - on Pytrack2 (only used for software development)

div.div:
Power
Input - 12v battery (sealed lead acid)
Outputs via 3 LM2596 DC-DC converters tuned for 4v, 5v and 9v
4v drives the SIM800L (needs 2A+)
5v drives the Lopy4 and the RS232 Level Shifter
9v drives the UHF reader
